    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3663" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπι-φράζομαι</span></b> , aor. 1 2 sing.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπεφράσω, 3 ἐπεφράσατο</span>, subj.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπιφράσσετ̓</span>, opt. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπιφρασσαίμεθα</span>, 3 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-αίατο</span>, pass. aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπεφράσθης</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">consider, mark, devise</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 15.444</span></i>; joined w. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νοεῖν</span> (Odysseus weeps), <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἀλκίνοος δέ μιν οἶος ἐπεφράσατ᾽ ἠδ̓ ἐνόησεν</span>, ‘remarked’
          and noted the fact, <i><span class="en">Od. 8.94</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">533,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 5.665</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> οἷον
            δὴ τὸν μῦθον ἐπεφράσθης ἀγορεῦσαι</span>, ‘didst take it into thy
          head’ to say, <i><span class="en">Od. 5.183</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
